---
title: Mushroom & Bacon “MLT” Sandos with Roasted Potato Wedges & Mixed Green Salad
description: We’re giving this classic summery sandwich a vegan makeover. You’ll sizzle sliced mushrooms with savory-sweet paprika for extra-delicious flavor, and pile them onto toasted sourdough along with fresh tomato slices, mixed greens, and a swipe of tangy vegan mayo. Roasted potato wedges and a simple green salad round out this plant-based plate.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/66b14d5f78d91450badf8142-5601a8a0.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/66b3ca38995e511e4eca9db1-en-US.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/mushroom-and-bacon-mlt-sandos-66b3ca38995e511e4eca9db1
cuisine: North America
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 880 kcal
  fat: 59 g
  saturated fat: 14 g
  carbohydrates: 75 g
  sugar: 8 g
  protein: 21 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 1120 mg
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of oil, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, trim and thinly slice @button mushrooms{8%ounce} (skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!). Quarter @lemon{1}. Thinly slice @tomato{1} into rounds; lightly season with salt and pepper.

Heat a large dry pan over medium-high heat. Add @bacon{4%ounce}; cook, turning occasionally and adjusting heat if browning too quickly, until crispy, ~{6-10%minutes}. Transfer bacon to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms, @paprika{1%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and slightly crispy, ~{5-7%minutes}.

> For perfect timing, start mushrooms when potatoes have 10 minutes left!

Meanwhile, toast @sourdough bread{4%slice} until golden.

Use pan used for bacon here.

In a #medium bowl{}, toss @mixed greens{2%ounce} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} and juice from one lemon wedge.

> Large drizzle of olive oil and juice from two wedges for 4 servings.

Spread @vegan mayonnaise{4%tablespoon} over sourdough slices. Top half the slices with mushrooms, tomato, and as much salad as you like. Close to form sandwiches.

Halve sandwiches and divide between plates. Serve with potato wedges, any remaining salad, and remaining lemon wedges on the side.

Top sourdough slices with bacon along with mushrooms and tomato.

> Bacon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.